1. What is the difference between an adaptive website and a fully responsive website?

    Adaptive web design is different from responsive design because there isn't one layout that always changes. Adaptive design has several distinct layouts for different screen sizes.

2. Describe what it means to be mobile first vs desktop first.

	Mobile first means designing a website for mobile before designing it for the desktop. Desktop first is the result responsive web which assumes visitors will browse it on a desktop computer.

3. What does font-size: 62.5% in the html tag do for us when using rem units?
	
    The 62.5% font-size makes px-rem calculation easier since the font sizes in px are 10 times their rem values.

4. How would you describe preprocessing to someone new to CSS?
	
    A CSS preprocessor is a program that generates CSS from the preprocessor's own unique syntax which adds some features that don't exist in pure CSS, such as mixin, nesting selector, inheritance selector, and so on.

5. What is your favorite concept in preprocessing? What is the concept that gives you the most trouble?
	
    Nesting selector is my favorite while mixin gives me the most trouble.
